jnxMvpnMIB.name: jnxMvpnMIB
jnxMvpnMIB.organization: IETF Layer-3 Virtual Private Networks Working Group.
jnxMvpnMIB.contactinfo: Jeffrey (Zhaohui) Zhang zzhang@juniper.net Comments and discussion to l3vpn@ietf.org
jnxMvpnMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for multicast in BGP/MPLS IP VPNs defined by [MVPN]. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2012).

jnxMvpnMvrfNumber.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumber
jnxMvpnMvrfNumber.description: The number of MVRFs for IPv4 or IPv6 or mLDP C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberV4.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberV4
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberV4.description: The number of MVRFs for IPv4 C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberV6.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberV6
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberV6.description: The number of MVRFs for IPv6 C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberPimV4.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberPimV4
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberPimV4.description: The number of PIM-MVPN MVRFs for IPv4 C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberPimV6.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberPimV6
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberPimV6.description: The number of PIM-MVPN MVRFs for IPv6 C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberBgpV4.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberBgpV4
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberBgpV4.description: The number of BGP-MVPN MVRFs for IPv4 C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberBgpV6.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberBgpV6
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberBgpV6.description: The number of BGP-MVPN MVRFs for IPv6 C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnMvrfNumberMldp.name: jnxMvpnMvrfNumberMldp
jnxMvpnMvrfNumberMldp.description: The number of BGP-MVPN MVRFs for mLDP C-Multicast that are present in this device.

jnxMvpnNotificationEnable.name: jnxMvpnNotificationEnable
jnxMvpnNotificationEnable.description: If this object is TRUE, then the generation of all notifications defined in this MIB is enabled.

jnxMvpnGeneralTable.name: jnxMvpnGeneralTable
jnxMvpnGeneralTable.description: This table specifies the general information about the MVRFs present in this device.

jnxMvpnGeneralEntry.name: jnxMvpnGeneralEntry
jnxMvpnGeneralEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every MVRF in the device.

jnxMvpnGenOperStatusChange.name: jnxMvpnGenOperStatusChange
jnxMvpnGenOperStatusChange.description: This object describes the last operational change that happened for the given MVRF. createdMvrf - indicates that the MVRF was created in the device. deletedMvrf - indicates that the MVRF was deleted from the device. A row in this table will never have mvpnGenOperStatusChange equal to deletedMvrf(2), because in that case the row itself will be deleted from the table. This value for mvpnGenOperStatusChange is defined mainly for use in mvpnMvrfChange notification. modifiedMvrfIpmsiConfig - indicates that the I-PMSI for the MVRF was configured, deleted or changed. modifiedMvrfSpmsiConfig - indicates that the S-PMSI for the MVRF was configured, deleted or changed.

jnxMvpnGenOperChangeTime.name: jnxMvpnGenOperChangeTime
jnxMvpnGenOperChangeTime.description: The time at which the last operational change for the MVRF in question took place. The last operational change is specified by mvpnGenOperStatusChange.

jnxMvpnGenCmcastRouteProtocolV4.name: jnxMvpnGenCmcastRouteProtocolV4
jnxMvpnGenCmcastRouteProtocolV4.description: Protocol used to signal IPv4 C-multicast states across the provider core. pim(1): PIM (PIM-MVPN). bgp(2): BGP (BGP-MVPN).

jnxMvpnGenCmcastRouteProtocolV6.name: jnxMvpnGenCmcastRouteProtocolV6
jnxMvpnGenCmcastRouteProtocolV6.description: Protocol used to signal IPv6 C-multicast states across the provider core. pim(1): PIM (PIM-MVPN). bgp(2): BGP (BGP-MVPN).

jnxMvpnGenIpmsiConfigV4.name: jnxMvpnGenIpmsiConfigV4
jnxMvpnGenIpmsiConfigV4.description: This points to a row in MvpnPmsiConfigTable, for I-PMSI configuration for IPv4.

jnxMvpnGenIpmsiConfigV6.name: jnxMvpnGenIpmsiConfigV6
jnxMvpnGenIpmsiConfigV6.description: This points to a row in MvpnPmsiConfigTable, for I-PMSI configuration for IPv6.

jnxMvpnGenInterAsPmsiConfigV4.name: jnxMvpnGenInterAsPmsiConfigV4
jnxMvpnGenInterAsPmsiConfigV4.description: This points to a row in MvpnPmsiConfigTable, for inter-as I-PMSI configuration for IPv4, in case of segmented inter-as provider tunnels.

jnxMvpnGenInterAsPmsiConfigV6.name: jnxMvpnGenInterAsPmsiConfigV6
jnxMvpnGenInterAsPmsiConfigV6.description: This points to a row in MvpnPmsiConfigTable, for inter-as I-PMSI configuration for IPv6, in case of segmented inter-as provider tunnels.

jnxMvpnGenRowStatus.name: jnxMvpnGenRowStatus
jnxMvpnGenRowStatus.description: This is used to create or delete a row in this table.

jnxMvpnBgpGeneralTable.name: jnxMvpnBgpGeneralTable
jnxMvpnBgpGeneralTable.description: This table augments the mvpnGeneralTable and is for BGP-MVPN specific information.

jnxMvpnBgpGeneralEntry.name: jnxMvpnBgpGeneralEntry
jnxMvpnBgpGeneralEntry.description: The mvpnBgpGeneralEntry matches and augments an mvpnGeneralEntry for a BGP-MVPN instance, with BGP-MVPN specific informatoin.

jnxMvpnBgpGenMode.name: jnxMvpnBgpGenMode
jnxMvpnBgpGenMode.description: For two different BGP-MVPN modes: rpt-spt(1): intersite-site shared tree mode spt-only(2): inter-site source-only tree mode.

jnxMvpnBgpGenUmhSelection.name: jnxMvpnBgpGenUmhSelection
jnxMvpnBgpGenUmhSelection.description: The UMH selection method for this mvpn, as specified in section 5.1.3 of [MVPN]: highest-pe-address (1): PE with the highest address c-root-group-hashing (2): hashing based on (c-root, c-group) uncast-umh-route (3): per ucast route towards c-root

jnxMvpnBgpGenSiteType.name: jnxMvpnBgpGenSiteType
jnxMvpnBgpGenSiteType.description: Whether this site is a receiver-only site or not. sender-receiver (1): both sender and receiver site. receiver-only (2): receiver-only site. sender-only (3): sender-only site.

jnxMvpnBgpGenCmcastImportRt.name: jnxMvpnBgpGenCmcastImportRt
jnxMvpnBgpGenCmcastImportRt.description: The C-multicast Import RT that this device adds to unicast vpn routes that it advertises for this mvpn.

jnxMvpnBgpGenSrcAs.name: jnxMvpnBgpGenSrcAs
jnxMvpnBgpGenSrcAs.description: The Source AS number in Source AS Extended Community that this device adds to the unicast vpn routes that it advertises for this mvpn.

jnxMvpnBgpGenSptnlLimit.name: jnxMvpnBgpGenSptnlLimit
jnxMvpnBgpGenSptnlLimit.description: The max number of selective provider tunnels this device allows for this mvpn.

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTable.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTable
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTable.description: This table specifies the configured PMSIs.

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigEntry.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigEntry
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for each PMSI configured on this router. It can be referred to by either I-PMSI configuration (in mvpnGeneralEntry) or S-PMSI configuration (in mvpnSpmsiConfigEntry)

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelType.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelType
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelType.description: Type of tunnel used to instantiate the PMSI.

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelAuxInfo.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelAuxInfo
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelAuxInfo.description: Additional tunnel information depending on the type. pim: In case of S-PMSI, number of groups starting at mvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddress. This allows a range of PIM provider tunnel group addresses to be specified in S-PMSI case. In I-PMSI case, it must be 1. rsvp-p2mp: 1 for statically specified rsvp-p2mp tunnel 2 for dynamically created rsvp-p2mp tunnel ingress-replication: 1 for using any existing p2p/mp2p lsp 2 for dynamically creating new p2p lsp

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddressTy.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddressType
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddressTy.description: In case of PIM provider tunnel, the type of tunnel address.

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddress.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddress
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelPimGroupAddress.description: In case of PIM provider tunnel, the provider tunnel address.

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelOrTemplateName.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelOrTemplateName
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigTunnelOrTemplateName.description: The tunnel name or template name used to create tunnels. Depending on mvpnPmsiConfigTunnelType and mvpnPmsiConfigTunnelAuxInfo: dynamically created rsvp-p2mp tunnel: template name statically specified rsvp-p2mp tunnel: tunnel name ingress-replication using dynamically created lsps: template name other: null

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigEncapsType.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigEncapsType
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigEncapsType.description: The encapsulation type to be used, in case of PIM tunnel or ingress-replication.

jnxMvpnPmsiConfigRowStatus.name: jnxMvpnPmsiConfigRowStatus
jnxMvpnPmsiConfigRowStatus.description: Used to create/modify/delete a row in this table.

jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigEntry.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigEntry
jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigEntry.description: An entry is created for each S-PMSI configuration.

jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigCmcastGroupPrefixLen.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigCmcastGroupPrefixLen
jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigCmcastGroupPrefixLen.description: C-multicast group address prefix length. A group 0 (or ::0) with prefix length 32 (or 128) indicates wildcard group, while a group 0 (or ::0) with prefix length 0 indicates any group.

jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigCmcastSourcePrefixLen.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigCmcastSourcePrefixLen
jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigCmcastSourcePrefixLen.description: C-multicast source address prefix length. A source 0 (or ::0) with prefix length 32 (or 128) indicates a wildcard source, while a source 0 (or ::0) with prefix length 0 indicates any source.

jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigThreshold.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigThreshold
jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigThreshold.description: The bandwidth threshold value which when exceeded for a multicast routing entry in the given MVRF, triggers usage of S-PMSI.

jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigPmsiPointer.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigPmsiPointer
jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigPmsiPointer.description: This points to a row in MvpnPmsiConfigTable, to specify tunnel attributes.

jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigRowStatus.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigRowStatus
jnxMvpnSpmsiConfigRowStatus.description: Used to create/modify/delete a row in this table.

jnxMvpnIpmsiTable.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiTable
jnxMvpnIpmsiTable.description: This table is for all advertised/received I-PMSI advertisements.

jnxMvpnIpmsiEntry.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiEntry
jnxMvpnIpmsiEntry.description: An entry in this table corresponds to an I-PMSI advertisement that is advertised/received on this router. This represents all the sender PEs in the MVPN, with the provider tunnel they use to send traffic.

jnxMvpnIpmsiAfi.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiAfi
jnxMvpnIpmsiAfi.description: The address family this I-PMSI is for. 1 - IPv4 2 - IPv6

jnxMvpnIpmsiRD.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiRD
jnxMvpnIpmsiRD.description: The Route Distinguisher in this I-PMSI.

jnxMvpnIpmsiOrigAddrType.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiOrigAddrType
jnxMvpnIpmsiOrigAddrType.description: The Internet address type of mvpnIpmsiOrigAddress.

jnxMvpnIpmsiOrigAddress.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiOrigAddress
jnxMvpnIpmsiOrigAddress.description: The BGP address of the device that originated the I-PMSI.

jnxMvpnIpmsiUpTime.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiUpTime
jnxMvpnIpmsiUpTime.description: The time since this I-PMSI was first advertised/received by the device.

jnxMvpnIpmsiAttribute.name: jnxMvpnIpmsiAttribute
jnxMvpnIpmsiAttribute.description: Points to a row in the mvpnPmsiTunnelAttributeTable.

jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiTable.name: jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiTable
jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiTable.description: This table is for all advertised/received inter-as I-PMSI advertisements.

jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiEntry.name: jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiEntry
jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiEntry.description: An entry in this table corresponds to an inter-as I-PMSI advertisement that is advertised/received on this router. This represents all the ASes in the MVPN, with the provider tunnel used to send traffic to.

jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiAfi.name: jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiAfi
jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiAfi.description: The address family this I-PMSI is for. 1 - IPv4 2 - IPv6

jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiRD.name: jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiRD
jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiRD.description: The Route Distinguisher in this inter-as I-PMSI.

jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiSrcAs.name: jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiSrcAs
jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiSrcAs.description: The source-as in this inter-as I-PMSI.

jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiAttribute.name: jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiAttribute
jnxMvpnInterasIpmsiAttribute.description: Points to a row in the mvpnPmsiTunnelAttributeTable.

jnxMvpnSpmsiTable.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiTable
jnxMvpnSpmsiTable.description: This table has information about the S-PMSIs sent/received by a device.

jnxMvpnSpmsiEntry.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiEntry
jnxMvpnSpmsiEntry.description: An entry in this table is created or updated for every S-PMSI advertised/received in a particular MVRF.

jnxMvpnSpmsiOrigAddrType.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiOrigAddrType
jnxMvpnSpmsiOrigAddrType.description: The Internet address type of mvpnSpmsiOrigAddress.

jnxMvpnSpmsiOrigAddress.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiOrigAddress
jnxMvpnSpmsiOrigAddress.description: The BGP address of the device that originated the S-PMSI.

jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastAddrType.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastAddrType
jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastAddrType.description: The Internet address type of mvpnSpmsiCmcastGroup/Source.

jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastGroup.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastGroup
jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastGroup.description: S-PMSI C-multicast group address. If it is 0 (or ::0), this is a wildcard group, and mvpnSpmsiCmcastGroupPrefixLen must be 32 (or 128).

jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastGroupPrefixLen.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastGroupPrefixLen
jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastGroupPrefixLen.description: S-PMSI C-multicast group address prefix length.

jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastSource.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastSource
jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastSource.description: S-PMSI C-multicast source address If it is 0 (or ::0), this is a wildcard source, and mvpnSpmsiCmcastSourcePrefixLen must be 32 (or 128).

jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastSourcePrefixLen.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastSourcePrefixLen
jnxMvpnSpmsiCmcastSourcePrefixLen.description: S-PMSI C-multicast source address prefix length.

jnxMvpnSpmsiTunnelAttribute.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiTunnelAttribute
jnxMvpnSpmsiTunnelAttribute.description: A row pointer to the mvpnPmsiTunnelAttributeTable

jnxMvpnSpmsiUpTime.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiUpTime
jnxMvpnSpmsiUpTime.description: The time since this S-PMSI was first advertised/received by the device.

jnxMvpnSpmsiExpTime.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiExpTime
jnxMvpnSpmsiExpTime.description: For UDP-based S-PMSI signaling for PIM-MVPN, the amount of time remaining before this received S-PMSI Join Message expires, or the next S-PMSI Join Message refresh is to be advertised again from the device. Otherwise, it is zero.

jnxMvpnSpmsiRefCnt.name: jnxMvpnSpmsiRefCnt
jnxMvpnSpmsiRefCnt.description: The number of c-multicast routes that are mapped to this S-PMSI.

jnxMvpnMrouteTable.name: jnxMvpnMrouteTable
jnxMvpnMrouteTable.description: This table augments ipMcastRouteTable, to provide some MVPN specific information.

jnxMvpnMrouteEntry.name: jnxMvpnMrouteEntry
jnxMvpnMrouteEntry.description: The mvpnMrouteEntry matches and augments an ipMcastRouteTable, with MVPN specific information, such as PMSI used.

jnxMvpnMroutePmsiPointer.name: jnxMvpnMroutePmsiPointer
jnxMvpnMroutePmsiPointer.description: The I-PMSI or S-PMSI this C-multicast route is using. This is important because an implementation may not have an interface corresponding to a provider tunnel, that can be used in ipMcastRouteNextHopEntry.

jnxMvpnMrouteNumberOfLocalReplication.name: jnxMvpnMrouteNumberOfLocalReplication
jnxMvpnMrouteNumberOfLocalReplication.description: Number of replications to local receivers.

jnxMvpnMrouteNumberOfRemoteReplication.name: jnxMvpnMrouteNumberOfRemoteReplication
jnxMvpnMrouteNumberOfRemoteReplication.description: Number of (local) replications to remote receivers.

jnxMvpnMrouteDataRate.name: jnxMvpnMrouteDataRate
jnxMvpnMrouteDataRate.description: The data rate for traffic following this route.

jnxMvpnMvrfChange.name: jnxMvpnMvrfChange
jnxMvpnMvrfChange.description: A mvpnMvrfChange notification signifies a change about a MVRF in the device. The change event can be creation of the MVRF, deletion of the MVRF or an update on the I-PMSI or S-PMSI configuration of the MVRF. The change event is indicated by mvpnGenOperStatusChange embedded in the notification. The user can then query mvpnGeneralTable, and/or mvpnSpmsiConfigTable to get the details of the change as necessary. Note: Since the creation of a MVRF is often followed by configuration of I-PMSI and/or S-PMSIs for the MVRF, more than one (three at most) notifications for a MVRF may be generated serially, and it is really not necessary to generate all three of them. An agent may choose to generate a notification for the last event only, that is for S-PMSI configuration. Similarly, deletion of I-PMSI and S-PMSI configuration on a MVRF happens before a MVRF is deleted and it is recommended that the agent send the notification for MVRF deletion event only.
